{"lemma":"فَخْذٌ","slug":"فَخْذٌ","root":"ف.خ.ذ","root_slug":"ف-خ-ذ","root_link":"/words/roots/ف-خ-ذ","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":6},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["","n33191"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%81%D9%8E%D8%AE%D9%92%D8%B0%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"thigh"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"a small sub-tribe, the portion consisting of one's nearest relatives"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to separate, to divide into groups"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to separate, to divide into groups; to divide one's tribe into factions"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to leave, to forsake"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"alternative form of فاخَذَ (fāḵaḏa)","tags":["alt-of","alternative"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"The family sense stemming from the Bedouin practice of sitting in close proximity, thigh against thigh, with those who are dearer or have closer relationship."},"ipa":["/fa.xið/","/faxð/","/fax.xa.ða/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n33191","headword_ar":"فَخِذٌ","root":"fx*","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faxo*N","text_ar":"فَخْذٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, L, Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fixo*N","text_ar":"فِخْذٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, L, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fixi*N","text_ar":"فِخِذٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (L, TA,) as Ez-Zarkashee says in his Expos. of El-Bukháree, (TA,) for in the case of every faucial medial radical of a word of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faEil","text_ar":"فَعِل"},{"kind":"text","text":", whether a noun like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faxi*N","text_ar":"فَخِذٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"or a verb like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ahida","text_ar":"شَهِدَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", there are four dial. vars., namely,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faEil","text_ar":"فَعِل"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faEol","text_ar":"فَعْل"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiEol","text_ar":"فِعْل"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiEil","text_ar":"فِعِل"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Seer, O, TA;) thus it is said in the Tes-heel of Ibn-Málik; and MF says that the first three forms are common to every word of the measure of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"katif","text_ar":"كَتِف"},{"kind":"text","text":"though without a faucial letter; (TA;) The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"thigh;"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e. the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"limb"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wSl","text_ar":"وصل"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wuiSol","text_ar":"وُِصْل"},{"kind":"text","text":", but in the O written"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waSol","text_ar":"وَصْل"},{"kind":"text","text":",])"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"between the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saAq","text_ar":"سَاق"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"warik","text_ar":"وَرِك"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Mgh, * O, L, K; *) so says Lth; (O;) and in this sense, the first of the forms above mentioned is the most chaste: (MF:) it is of the fem. gender: (Mgh, O, L, Msb, K:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^afoxaA*N","text_ar":"اَفْخَاذٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Sb, L, Msb, K,) the only pl. form. (Sb, L.) ―         -b2-  Also (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A small sub-tribe,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"portion of the tribe, consisting of the nearest of the kinsfolk"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a man; (Kh, A, * O, L, K; *)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"less than a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baTon","text_ar":"بَطْن"},{"kind":"text","text":"; the first [i. e. largest] body being the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aEob","text_ar":"شَعْب"},{"kind":"text","text":", then the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qabiylap","text_ar":"قَبِيلَة"},{"kind":"text","text":", then the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faSiylap","text_ar":"فَصِيلَة"},{"kind":"text","text":", then the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EimaArap","text_ar":"عِمَارَة"},{"kind":"text","text":", then the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baTon","text_ar":"بَطْن"},{"kind":"text","text":", and then the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faxoi*","text_ar":"فَخِْذ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, O, L:) or it is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"below the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qabiylap","text_ar":"قَبِيلَة"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"but above the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baTon","text_ar":"بَطْن"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and is pronounced with the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"x","text_ar":"خ"},{"kind":"text","text":"quiescent: (IDrd, O:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"below the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faSiylap","text_ar":"فَصِيلَة"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"but above the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baTon","text_ar":"بَطْن"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Msb:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"below the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baTon","text_ar":"بَطْن"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and above the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faSiylap","text_ar":"فَصِيلَة"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Mgh, Msb:) this last, accord. to IB and Aboo-Usámeh, is the true order; (TA voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$Eb","text_ar":"شعب"},{"kind":"text","text":", q. v.;) and AM says that the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faSiylap","text_ar":"فَصِيلَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"is nearer than the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fx*","text_ar":"فخذ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (L:) in this sense, the second of the forms above mentioned is the most chaste: (MF:) and in this sense it is of the masc. gender; (A, Mgh, O, Msb;) because meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nafarN","text_ar":"نَفَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Msb;) wherefore you say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h`*aA faxo*iY","text_ar":"هٰذَا فَخْذِى"},{"kind":"text","text":": (A:) pl. as above. (A, O, L, K.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hulibati Aln~aAqapu","text_ar":"حُلِبَتِ النَّاقَةُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiY faxi*ihaA","text_ar":"فِى فَخِذِهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"is a phrase mentioned by Fr, meaning (assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The she-camel was milked"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in her half-month"},{"kind":"text","text":"[app."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"at the period commencing half a month after her parturition"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (O.)"}],"source_refs":["S","O","L","Msb","K","TA","MF","Mgh","Sb","IDrd","A"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}